  <h1>Juca</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Frontend for lawyers</p>

  <span class="badge badge-alpha">alpha</span>

  <p>
    Juca is the frontend through which legal professionals interact with the
    sens.legal ecosystem. It consumes Valter's REST API to provide search,
    analysis, and case management capabilities in a web interface designed
    for the workflow of Brazilian lawyers.
  </p>

  <h2>Stack</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Framework:</strong> Next.js 15</li>
    <li><strong>Language:</strong> TypeScript</li>
    <li><strong>UI:</strong> React, Tailwind CSS</li>
    <li><strong>State:</strong> React Server Components + client hooks</li>
    <li><strong>Deploy:</strong> Vercel</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Key Capabilities</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Jurisprudence search with filters (minister, date, category, result)</li>
    <li>Case briefing workflow with guided phase analysis</li>
    <li>Document viewer with IRAC enrichment</li>
    <li>Canvas for organizing legal arguments</li>
    <li>Integration with Valter's anti-hallucination verification</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Status</h2>

  <p>
    Juca is in active development. The rewrite (Waves 0-5) was completed in
    February 2026, establishing the foundation for the briefing workflow, canvas,
    and search interface. Authentication and multi-user features are planned but
    not yet available.
  </p>

  <h2>Roadmap</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>User authentication and multi-tenant support</li>
    <li>Case management dashboard</li>
    <li>Document annotation and collaboration</li>
    <li>Mobile-responsive interface</li>
  </ul>

